captions.text:
Would everyone love
to hear ron burgundy
play "yazz" flute?

- Get it goin', ron!
- Yes!  Please.

Okay, I guess I can play
a little ditty.

- Give him a hand.
- I'm not prepared.
Not at all.

- Yeah!
- This is a surprise,
I'll tell you.

And, jay, let's take
the bass line for a walk.

We got it now.
It's all right.

Little "ham
and eggs" comin' at you.
Hope you got your griddles.

That's baby-makin' music,
that's what that is.

+Ryan Pragovich not sure why I give a $#!+, but Ian Anderson was the 
musician, the band was "Jethro Tull", named after a dude who, according to 
the all knowing Google, was an English agricultural pioneer from Berkshire 
who helped bring about the British Agricultural Revolution. He perfected a 
horse-drawn seed drill in 1701 that economically sowed the seeds in neat 
rows, and later a horse-drawn hoe. Tull's methods were adopted by many 
large landowners, and they helped form the basis of modern agriculture.

Now you know!  And Knowing is half the battle!  Go Joe!
